{
  "doc_id": "11647",
  "text": "In recent years, the NanoString technology Lymph2Cx assay was developed based on GEP, which shows a strong concordance to the original COO model and can be applied on FFPE tissue. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] This assay uses a limited set of 15 pre-specified genes and five housekeeping genes, and has the potential to identify all three subgroups of DLBCL. [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] In this study, our aim was to investigate the concordance between the Lymph2Cx assay and the IHC algorithm by Hans et al. [CITATION_7] in relation to clinical characteristics, tumor markers and survival outcome. This was to identify which model would be the best survival predictor in a large cohort of Swedish and Danish DLBCL patients (n = 359).",
